description.narrative:
The project, implemented by UNHCR, is financed with a voluntary contribution of 2 million euros and foresees a duration of 1 year. This project aims to ensure the protection needs of: i) returned Afghan refugees, ii) Afghan internal refugees (IDPs) iii) vulnerable communities, including mixed populations (residents and refugees), in urban and peri-urban areas with a high number of refugees with particular emphasis on women.

The project will contribute to achieving UNHCR's overall strategic objectives:
1) Facilitating the voluntary repatriation of Afghan refugees;
2) Support peaceful co-existence between host communities and registered repatriated refugees to make integration more sustainable;
3) Strengthen services for registered and vulnerable repatriated refugees, IDPs and refugees identified through the "People with Specific Needs" (NDP) program.

The activities will include:
• Management of four "Registration Centers" (encashment centers) and payment of the cash grant for returned and registered refugees;
• "Community Based" protection activities updated through protection monitoring.
• Assistance to people with specific needs. 
The direct beneficiaries will be 6,500 refugees returning to Afghanistan who will receive the "Cash Grants" and 600 repatriated refugees and IDPs with specific needs. The project also foresees four "community based" protection initiatives in areas of resettlement of repatriates and / or IDPs, which will also benefit local populations.
